<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/22751054-jaye-knight"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1624967837i/22751054._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/22751054-jaye-knight">Jaye Knight</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It depends. For most people, I suggest reading Resistance first because Half-Blood is depressing (though has a hopeful ending), and I don&apos;t want them <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It depends. For most people, I suggest reading Resistance first because Half-Blood is depressing (though has a hopeful ending), and I don't want them to get scared off the rest of the series. But for anyone who doesn't think that is an issue, Half-Blood can be read first. :)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
