<div id="review_1714952882" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1714952882" />
    <a title="R.J. Rodda" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4123340-r-j-rodda"><img alt="R.J. Rodda" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1466825325p2/4123340.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1714952882?book_show_action=true">Jul 31, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="R.J. Rodda" class="user" itemprop="url" name="R.J. Rodda" href="/user/show/4123340-r-j-rodda">R.J. Rodda</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4123340-r-j-rodda?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4123340-r-j-rodda?shelf=christian">christian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1714952882" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9615017509348413028">This is the back story of Jace from &apos;Resistance&apos; (Ilyon Chronicles Book 1). If you like Jace, as I do, it is a must-read. Do read &apos;Resistance&apos; first though. Jace&apos;s story is essentially sad, except for the end. I was expecting a harrowing story and it was, but some scenes were cut short and the cruelty was not as detailed as it could have been for which I was grateful. Most of the material in this is not new, in the sense that it tallies from what we know in Resistance but it is from Jace&apos;s point</span>
  <span id="freeText9615017509348413028" style="display:none">This is the back story of Jace from 'Resistance' (Ilyon Chronicles Book 1). If you like Jace, as I do, it is a must-read. Do read 'Resistance' first though. Jace's story is essentially sad, except for the end. I was expecting a harrowing story and it was, but some scenes were cut short and the cruelty was not as detailed as it could have been for which I was grateful. Most of the material in this is not new, in the sense that it tallies from what we know in Resistance but it is from Jace's point of view and fleshed out. I haven't liked a character as much as him in a long time, and I think he's worth his own book. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="9615017509348413028" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


