    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1348980856" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1348980856" />
    <a title="Sarah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/45502602-sarah"><img alt="Sarah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1492360095p2/45502602.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1348980856?book_show_action=true">Jul 29, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sarah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sarah" href="/user/show/45502602-sarah">Sarah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/45502602-sarah?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1348980856" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9879461181877914144">The Ilyon Chronicles are fast becoming my favorite book series, so I was thrilled when my younger sister allowed me to read her copy of &quot;Half Blood&quot;. <br/> It was really neat to be let into the secret world of Jace, and see what he was like before &quot;Resistance&quot; (book 1 of the Ilyon Chronicles) <br/> It was quite depressing. I kept turning page after page waiting for things to get better, unfortunately things got a lot worse before they got better. .I would have liked to see at least one or two people show </span>
  <span id="freeText9879461181877914144" style="display:none">The Ilyon Chronicles are fast becoming my favorite book series, so I was thrilled when my younger sister allowed me to read her copy of "Half Blood". <br /> It was really neat to be let into the secret world of Jace, and see what he was like before "Resistance" (book 1 of the Ilyon Chronicles) <br /> It was quite depressing. I kept turning page after page waiting for things to get better, unfortunately things got a lot worse before they got better. .I would have liked to see at least one or two people show kindness to Jace. The reason being it didn't make sense to me that after a lifetime of being mistreated and hated on by every person he came into contact with, why he would have such a high standard of the quality of human life. I guess this just proves that Jace has a big heart contrary to what everyone wants him to think. <br /> I was disappointed that I didn't get to meet Jace's parents. I'm hoping that Jaye L. Knight writes what happened to them somewhere in the future of Ilyon. <br /> The ending was so wonderful and hopeful! It was like a rainbow of promise of good things yet to happen in Jace. The ending was totally awesome and I am so pumped for the release of Samara's Peril, CANT WAIT!</span>
  <a data-text-id="9879461181877914144" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


